esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when container CPU usage exceeds 95% of its limit or node allocation.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Containers consuming more than 95% of CPU limits, indicating throttling risk.
//
// Grouped by cluster, container name, and namespace to identify the specific
// container experiencing high CPU usage.
//
// To reduce noise, increase the threshold (e.g., doc_count > 5).
TS metrics-kubernetes.container-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.container.cpu.usage.limit.pct` > 0.95
  OR `kubernetes.container.cpu.usage.node.pct` > 0.95
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.container.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
